<subSubSection id="8684427ABCF9483AAE21E92043E07D3A" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="common name">
<paragraph id="8935E1B27AB808CC174659F876F0701B" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Common name.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CE15FE8D04338F03F492DC3D9747BB4C" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
Gaan busi Mulumba (Paramaka; 
<bibRefCitation id="B88224125DA887707EDC86A1517EBD47" author="Sabatier, D" journalOrPublisher="Missouri Botanical Garden Press" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" publicationUrl="https://sciencepress.mnhn.fr/sites/default/files/articles/pdf/a1997n2a8.pdf" refId="B63" refString="Sabatier, D, 1997. Description et biologie d'une nouvelle espece de Virola (Myristicaceae) de Guyane. Adansonia ser. 3 19(2): 273-278. https://sciencepress.mnhn.fr/sites/default/files/articles/pdf/a1997n2a8.pdf" title="Description et biologie d'une nouvelle espece de Virola (Myristicaceae) de Guyane. Adansonia ser. 3 19 (2): 273 - 278." url="https://sciencepress.mnhn.fr/sites/default/files/articles/pdf/a1997n2a8.pdf" year="1997">Sabatier 1997</bibRefCitation>
). French Guiana: yayamadou, yayamadou montagne (
<normalizedToken id="0B0FE0910FA1E774FBDDD652670F9096" originalValue="Créole">Creole</normalizedToken>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="5F5EE318DBE54399736A13CEEC29F332" author="Mitchell, JD" editor="Mori, SA" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of The New York Botanical Garden 76 (2)" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" pagination="525 - 532" refId="B46" refString="Mitchell, JD, 2002. Myristicaceae (Nutmeg Family). In: Mori, SA, Cremers, G, Gracie, CA, de Granville, JJ, Heald, SV, Hoff, M, Mitchell, JD, Eds., Guide to the vascular plants of Central French Guiana. Memoirs of The New York Botanical Garden 76(2): 525 - 532" title="Myristicaceae (Nutmeg Family)." volumeTitle="Guide to the vascular plants of Central French Guiana." year="2002">Mitchell 2002</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F3338051F9652E4A74921CE7D011C295" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="B961B50A7548093FA95DE215A1CFCA86" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7A853D5126087B0AE3F414E5E92A718B" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
The specific epithet alludes to the Spider monkeys, or ateles (
<taxonomicName id="EE895D2FEE2D8BD433641CB9BD629D28" class="Mammalia" family="Atelidae" genus="Ateles" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ateles panisczis" order="Primates" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="panisczis">
<emphasis id="0F98D27C98DF929CF805009BA5FB2781" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Ateles panisczis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), locally called kwata, who consume the fruits of this species (
<bibRefCitation id="DB019B9A19AA07C2765C292841201F05" author="Sabatier, D" journalOrPublisher="Missouri Botanical Garden Press" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" publicationUrl="https://sciencepress.mnhn.fr/sites/default/files/articles/pdf/a1997n2a8.pdf" refId="B63" refString="Sabatier, D, 1997. Description et biologie d'une nouvelle espece de Virola (Myristicaceae) de Guyane. Adansonia ser. 3 19(2): 273-278. https://sciencepress.mnhn.fr/sites/default/files/articles/pdf/a1997n2a8.pdf" title="Description et biologie d'une nouvelle espece de Virola (Myristicaceae) de Guyane. Adansonia ser. 3 19 (2): 273 - 278." url="https://sciencepress.mnhn.fr/sites/default/files/articles/pdf/a1997n2a8.pdf" year="1997">Sabatier 1997</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="93C996603D1CD9D9464CFE2E06A16287" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="notes">
<paragraph id="81B9FF1DBC6DE0AD381E7B67928CF304" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E8149DCDEFA302DDEF25E3EF56AC27D1" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<taxonomicName id="D8715E213C7A27F85C655DEE9823B8EE" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myristicaceae" genus="Virola" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Virola kwatae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Spermatophyta" rank="species" species="kwatae">
<emphasis id="8B1EC45E0FEA692DE142D6FFD075DE93" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Virola kwatae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was previously known from French Guiana. However, in a recent study of herbarium specimens at New York Botanical Garden, a collection with fruit made in 
<normalizedToken id="1BA5774784947015FD2F11BB359C9DFF" originalValue="Amapá">Amapa</normalizedToken>
state, Brazil was located. To our knowledge this represents the first record of this species among the Flora of Brazil.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
